  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      It is the primary purpose of this pilot study to investigate if physical therapy with
      strength training is better at improving muscle and gait function after anti-spastic
      treatment with Botulinum toxin compared to physical therapy without strength training in
      children with cerebral palsy. The investigators hypothesize that it is.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
